1
00:00:02,878 --> 00:00:06,507
["Ace of Spades" playing]

2
00:00:08,717 --> 00:00:09,718
[music fades]

3
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:12,304
- [chattering]
- [footsteps]

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:14,806
[high-pitched ringing]

5
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:16,934
[elevator bell dings]

6
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:18,393
What?

7
00:00:18,477 --> 00:00:21,355
- [Ms. Cobel] I said, "Are you all right?"
- Yeah, I'm fine.

8
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:26,235
Maybe you should talk to your sister.
It's an important decision.

9
00:00:26,318 --> 00:00:28,153
- My sister?
- Yes.

10
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:31,448
- Mark?
- Yeah.

11
00:00:31,949 --> 00:00:33,450
Are you sure you're okay?

12
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:37,704
Yes. I'm sorry, I just, uh...
I got a little woozy and then, um...

13
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,749
I'm gonna stop by the bathroom.

14
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,586
Uh-uh. I think it's the other way.

15
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:50,509
Right.

16
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:03,021
[high-pitched ringing]

17
00:01:03,105 --> 00:01:06,108
["Ace of Spades" resumes]

18
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:36,597
[music fades]

19
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,516
[Natalie] I don't know if I hate senators
or congressmen more.

20
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,601
[Helly] Hmm?

21
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:42,978
How many of those have you had?

22
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:44,605
[Helly] Just this one.

23
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:48,025
Good. We need you nimble.
We gotta get down there. You're on in 20.

24
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,987
I was on with the Board earlier.
They're really grateful for this.

25
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:55,157
- Gabby.
- Natalie, hello.

26
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:56,783
Hi.

27
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:00,746
Oh, Gabby,
this is Helena Eagan. [chuckles]

28
00:02:01,914 --> 00:02:06,001
My gosh.
Helena, so good to finally meet you.

29
00:02:08,544 --> 00:02:09,545
Likewise.

30
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:53,025
[breathes heavily]

31
00:03:53,525 --> 00:03:55,360
[machinery beeping]

32
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:08,624
[breathes heavily]

33
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:15,130
This better be working, assholes.

34
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,021
[sighs]

35
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:33,565
[breathes shakily]

36
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,651
Where am I?

37
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:39,321
Where am I?

38
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,788
[Devon] Mark. You okay, milady?

39
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,000
So Rebeck smells weird.

40
00:04:52,668 --> 00:04:54,253
Rebeck smells weird?

41
00:04:54,336 --> 00:04:57,297
Yeah, she was making chewing noises,
but she was not chewing.

42
00:04:57,381 --> 00:05:00,384
Just be prepared 'cause you might have to
share a book with her.

43
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:01,927
- A book, right.
- Mm-hmm.

44
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:04,072
The one you forgot to bring
even though I did remind you.

45
00:05:04,096 --> 00:05:06,557
- Right. Yeah, I'm sure... Uh, sorry.
- Mm-hmm.

46
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,433
- [Eleanor cooing]
- [Devon] That's okay.

47
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:09,518
Okay.

48
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:12,729
Okay.

49
00:05:12,813 --> 00:05:14,022
- How's our baby?
- Mm-hmm.

50
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:16,692
Um, our... [laughs]

51
00:05:16,775 --> 00:05:19,045
I'm gonna assume you mean that
in the "it takes a village" sense.

52
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:20,571
And she's good. She's hungry.

53
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:25,158
Oh. Um, I wanna have the life change talk.
I just need to pump before I die.

54
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:27,369
- I'll be really fast. Okay.
- Uh... Okay.

55
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:32,374
[sighs]

56
00:05:36,712 --> 00:05:40,716
["Ace of Spades" playing]

57
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:41,800
[music ends]

58
00:05:47,431 --> 00:05:48,974
[dog pants]

59
00:05:54,229 --> 00:05:55,230
[dog whimpers]

60
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,817
[floorboard creaking]

61
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,958
Hey. Hi. Hi.

62
00:06:26,637 --> 00:06:27,721
"Radar."

63
00:06:28,263 --> 00:06:30,307
- [chattering]
- [Patton] What's the thesis?

64
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,643
[Danise] I agree. It's very confused.

65
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:35,270
[Patton] Mark, hello. [chuckles]

66
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:37,731
Oh, hey, guys. What's up?

67
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:45,322
- Patton, no.
- Um, Mark, we were just discussing whether it might have been a wiser move for your sister to put off introducing the child until after tonight's event.

68
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:47,199
Mark, you don't have to weigh in on that.

69
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:51,161
- Obviously the child is an absolute angel.
- Wait... That's my sister? With the baby?

70
00:06:51,245 --> 00:06:53,205
Exactly, it's his sister.

71
00:06:53,288 --> 00:06:54,873
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

72
00:06:57,543 --> 00:06:59,002
- Well, that was awkward.
- Mmm.

73
00:07:00,254 --> 00:07:05,133
Okay, so my sister has the baby.
And Cobel is here?

74
00:07:08,262 --> 00:07:10,264
I've been asked to share my book with you.

75
00:07:11,348 --> 00:07:13,100
So I've heard. Uh, Rebecca?

76
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:16,687
Rebeck. I have small eyes,
so I have to read pretty close.

77
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:17,771
Okay. Well, I'm...

78
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:19,857
I'm sure that'll be fine.
If you'll excuse me?

79
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:22,401
And I have some sores
on the back of my head from my bird.

80
00:07:22,484 --> 00:07:23,735
- You might see them.
- Okay.

81
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,154
Hey.

82
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:28,490
Hello, Mark.

83
00:07:29,408 --> 00:07:33,579
I pumped, so it's Miller time.
Okay, so life change. What's happening?

84
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:39,209
We're, um... This is gonna sound weird…

85
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,377
[Devon chuckles]

86
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,088
We're close, you and I?

87
00:07:44,006 --> 00:07:46,425
[chuckles] What do you... What's going on?

88
00:07:47,593 --> 00:07:48,677
Can we talk privately?

89
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:57,274
- I... I... I just have to...
- [Ricken] Okay, my dearest ones, uh, we are nearing that hour, so if you'd all peacefully waft in the living room… Okay. Let's talk at the first reflection break.

90
00:07:57,311 --> 00:07:58,312
- Okay?
- Okay.

91
00:08:31,595 --> 00:08:34,282
[Gabby, echoing] You just don't realize
how much kids are gonna change your life.

92
00:08:34,306 --> 00:08:35,557
[normal voice] But they do.

93
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:39,352
- Uh, how many kids do you have?
- Just gave birth to my third.

94
00:08:39,937 --> 00:08:41,270
I should've stopped at two.

95
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:43,398
- Hey, there you are.
- Hey.

96
00:08:43,482 --> 00:08:45,734
- Angelo, great to see you.
- [Angelo] You too.

97
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:49,238
Helena, this is my husband, Angelo Arteta.

98
00:08:49,321 --> 00:08:51,490
Helena, nice to meet you.

99
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:52,741
I've gotta hop backstage.

100
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:54,010
- I'll see you in a second.
- Okay.

101
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:55,536
[Angelo] Lovely to see you, Natalie.

102
00:08:57,246 --> 00:08:59,498
- You okay?
- [sighs] She couldn't find the bottle.

103
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:00,624
Ah.

104
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,459
S-S... Wow. Three kids.

105
00:09:02,543 --> 00:09:04,545
Couldn't have done it
without a little help.

106
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:08,966
I mean, the idea that
people would want to outlaw severance.

107
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,344
Mm-hmm. I kn... I know.

108
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:30,529
[rolling trunk]

109
00:09:31,572 --> 00:09:34,116
[Angelo] The photo display is very moving.

110
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:38,161
I already knew how I'd be voting,
but I think...

111
00:09:38,245 --> 00:09:44,459
Well, seeing that and seeing you
and hearing what you have to say, all of this could really make a difference.

112
00:09:44,543 --> 00:09:47,462
Mmm. I hope... I hope so.

113
00:09:48,255 --> 00:09:49,882
Let's change some minds.

114
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,801
Well, I'm certainly gonna try.

115
00:09:52,885 --> 00:09:53,719
[Gabby chuckles]

116
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:54,803
Thank you.

117
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:58,682
And please
thank your father if you see him.

118
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:03,270
I will.

119
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:05,189
[bell ringing]

120
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:15,407
[bell ringing]

121
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:17,117
[Rebeck] Mark. Come here.

122
00:10:18,994 --> 00:10:20,204
Saved us a seat.

123
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:27,127
I just have to find my glasses.

124
00:10:28,712 --> 00:10:31,547
Mark, can you just hold that - for a second? - Yeah.

125
00:10:37,012 --> 00:10:38,805
[bell ringing]

126
00:10:40,349 --> 00:10:41,350
Oh, my God.

127
00:10:43,936 --> 00:10:55,280
Sorry, you can't unring - the bell-ringing app apparently. - [crowd laughs] [Ricken] Okay. Thank you all for being here.

128
00:10:56,031 --> 00:11:00,994
Um, before we start, there is one person that I would like to thank first and foremost.

129
00:11:01,078 --> 00:11:05,958
Uh, family is both my bedrock
and my inspiration.

130
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:11,713
So I dedicate the reading
to my firstborn daughter, who is here tonight.

131
00:11:11,797 --> 00:11:14,091
Eleanor, I love you.

132
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:16,885
[Devon sniffles]

133
00:11:19,763 --> 00:11:20,764
[Ricken clears throat]

134
00:11:20,848 --> 00:11:22,724
[whispers] My brother-in-law.

135
00:11:22,808 --> 00:11:26,144
[Ricken] And with that… I begin.

136
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:36,864
"It's said that as a child, Wolfgang Mozart killed another boy by slamming his head in a piano.

137
00:11:38,323 --> 00:11:39,575
Don't worry.

138
00:11:39,658 --> 00:11:42,619
My research for this book
has proven the claim untrue.

139
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:48,125
As your heart rate settles though, - consider the power an author…" - Mark.

140
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:50,836
- Can I look at her book too?
- Mm-hmm.

141
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:51,962
I can crane.

142
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:54,047
- [Ricken] "…can hold over a reader…"
- Sure.

143
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:57,301
[Ricken] "…heretofore called 'you.'

144
00:11:58,594 --> 00:12:02,806
But what, indeed, is 'you'?"

145
00:12:02,890 --> 00:12:03,950
[Angelo] Good luck tonight.

146
00:12:03,974 --> 00:12:05,601
It was great to meet you, Helena.

147
00:12:07,227 --> 00:12:12,024
[Ricken] "How can 'you'
mean different things to millions of readers around a vast Earth?

148
00:12:13,525 --> 00:12:18,488
And perhaps, most importantly,
who are you?"

149
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:35,756
[breathes heavily]

150
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:37,466
[machinery beeping]

151
00:13:02,908 --> 00:13:03,909
[lock clicks]

152
00:13:42,239 --> 00:13:43,782
[trunk jiggles]

153
00:13:50,747 --> 00:14:00,382
[Ricken] "All creatures,
from the leaping cat to the cowering shrew, think of themselves as 'you, ' a logical center for the universe.

154
00:14:00,465 --> 00:14:07,890
Yet the cat eats the shrew,
and we, like Schrödinger, live on to wonder what it means."

155
00:14:08,891 --> 00:14:09,933
End of chapter.

156
00:14:10,017 --> 00:14:11,852
[applause]

157
00:14:14,313 --> 00:14:19,359
[Ricken] Let's all take a, uh, seven-minute reflection break and then come back.

158
00:14:20,527 --> 00:14:23,197
Uh, Balf. Prepare the neti pot.

159
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,698
It was transformative.

160
00:14:25,282 --> 00:14:27,326
I'm gonna have to change my name again.

161
00:14:27,409 --> 00:14:31,413
What a wordsmith. He seemed to have
a little something in his throat.

162
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:33,123
- Oh, yeah.
- Hey.

163
00:14:33,207 --> 00:14:34,847
I'm gonna see if she'll have more bottle.

164
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,686
Give me a couple of minutes,
then meet me in the baby room?

165
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:37,711
- Okay.
- Okay.

166
00:14:42,299 --> 00:14:43,300
Excuse me.

167
00:14:51,475 --> 00:14:52,643
[Ricken breathes deeply]

168
00:14:53,227 --> 00:14:55,646
Um, Mr. Hale... Ricken?

169
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:59,233
I don't know why
my voice shakes like that.

170
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:05,239
I sound like a sad old hamburger waiter… [inhales shakily] …prattling on about sauces.

171
00:15:05,739 --> 00:15:07,616
"Hamburger waiter." What the fuck is that?

172
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:10,327
Jesus, why do I ever
open my buffoon mouth?

173
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:11,328
It's going great.

174
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:14,498
- I mean, the book is brilliant, and...
- Okay, Mark.

175
00:15:14,581 --> 00:15:16,142
Thank you, but you don't have to say that.

176
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:18,001
I'm well aware of
how I come across to you.

177
00:15:18,085 --> 00:15:23,423
- What? No, I mean it.
- [sighs] The... Your book, it... It opened up the world for me.

178
00:15:25,509 --> 00:15:26,844
Mark, are you okay?

179
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:30,931
Yes. This book changed my whole life.

180
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,475
You actually read it?

181
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:35,978
Ricken, are we friends?

182
00:15:36,728 --> 00:15:38,188
[sighs]

183
00:15:38,272 --> 00:15:42,901
Look, I know I sometimes
make you feel "less than" for having had the procedure.

184
00:15:42,985 --> 00:15:44,111
And I regret that.

185
00:15:44,945 --> 00:15:47,865
You had to deal with Gemma's passing
in a way that was best for you.

186
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:56,707
You know, I was scrolling through
old pictures this morning, and I found one of the four of us on the crest hike.

187
00:15:56,790 --> 00:16:00,586
- You remember the funny bees? [laughs]
- Do you have that on you? The picture?

188
00:16:00,669 --> 00:16:07,593
Yeah, sure. I should.
[inhales sharply] Um… - Uh, Ricken. The neti pot is warm. - Oh, thank you, Balf.

189
00:16:07,676 --> 00:16:09,761
Mark, I need to flush my sinuses.

190
00:16:09,845 --> 00:16:12,973
But thank you. You have no idea
how much this has meant to me.

191
00:16:24,234 --> 00:16:26,028
Mark, I was worried about you.

192
00:16:26,111 --> 00:16:27,613
Oh, I'm fine. Thanks, uh...

193
00:16:27,696 --> 00:16:29,865
I'm just going to check on my sister.

194
00:16:29,948 --> 00:16:35,204
[chuckles] Oh.
Um, when you hugged me before, you suddenly became tense. What was that?

195
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:38,248
[stammers] Oh, I didn't know I did.

196
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:41,043
Well, you did. You're tense now.

197
00:16:41,126 --> 00:16:44,254
Yeah, uh... Sorry, it's just parties.

198
00:16:44,338 --> 00:16:46,840
Did you mean what you said before?

199
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:49,051
About your plans.

200
00:16:51,303 --> 00:16:52,304
Of course.

201
00:16:53,931 --> 00:16:55,057
Tell me more.

202
00:16:59,269 --> 00:17:02,439
You know, I... I'm so sorry. I-I'm just...
I'm on uncle duty for my sister.

203
00:17:02,523 --> 00:17:04,066
So I-I'll be right back.

204
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:05,651
- Okay?
- Okay.

205
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:08,028
Okay. Thanks, Ms. Cobel.

206
00:17:56,368 --> 00:17:58,078
- [Eleanor crying]
- [Devon] I know.

207
00:17:58,161 --> 00:18:00,431
- Hey, there you are.
- Hey, I really need to talk to you.

208
00:18:00,455 --> 00:18:02,767
No, I know. I just have to deal with her.
She's having a meltdown.

209
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,144
But j-just meet me in there, okay?

210
00:18:04,168 --> 00:18:07,171
- Okay, I'll just... Wait. Uh, okay.
- I promise I'll be back.

211
00:18:09,131 --> 00:18:10,924
[crying continues]

212
00:18:11,008 --> 00:18:14,303
[shushing, murmurs]

213
00:18:14,386 --> 00:18:16,013
Oh, thank God, Mrs. Selvig. Hi.

214
00:18:16,096 --> 00:18:18,098
Can you take her for a sec
while I talk to Mark?

215
00:18:18,182 --> 00:18:20,225
- Of course, love.
- Thank you.

216
00:18:20,309 --> 00:18:22,060
- Is Mark all right?
- Yeah, he's fine.

217
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:23,395
Thank you, you're an angel.

218
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:27,107
- [Eleanor cries]
- [shushing]

219
00:18:28,025 --> 00:18:29,318
[shushes]

220
00:18:35,199 --> 00:18:38,368
Okay… I'm all yours.

221
00:18:50,923 --> 00:18:53,467
My name is Helena,
and I'm an Eagan. [laughs]

222
00:18:55,177 --> 00:18:59,348
So one of the things you learn
growing up as an Eagan is that the workers are our family.

223
00:18:59,431 --> 00:19:07,356
And I remember being confused
about that as a kid, because I thought that meant I had a few hundred thousand literal brothers and sisters scattered around the world. [chuckles]

224
00:19:07,439 --> 00:19:08,565
Oh, my God.

225
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:12,402
But as I grew older,
I learned that it's about shared ideals.

226
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:13,737
Um... [chuckles]

227
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:20,744
My dad used to make me
recite the nine core principles before bed every night, which I can't say I always did happily. Sorry, Dad.

228
00:19:20,827 --> 00:19:27,292
But those are now the values that I share
with everyone who works at Lumon, and that's what makes them my family.

229
00:19:27,918 --> 00:19:33,382
[echoing] And I would never ever ask them
to do anything that I'm not willing or excited to do myself.

230
00:19:33,465 --> 00:19:44,017
[normal voice] Oh. Look,
m-my dad would love for me to sit here and say that I'm taking this job out of loyalty and that it was the spirit of pure Eagan calling me to service.

231
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:49,690
But I took a severed job because
it sounds freaking awesome.

232
00:19:50,482 --> 00:19:52,860
So, no,
I don't think severance divides us.

233
00:19:53,694 --> 00:19:55,195
I think it brings us together.

234
00:20:11,879 --> 00:20:13,714
[tires squealing]

235
00:20:14,464 --> 00:20:15,465
[Mr. Milchick] Greetings.

236
00:20:15,549 --> 00:20:17,926
- I'm not here right now.
- Goddamn it, Milchick!

237
00:20:19,928 --> 00:20:21,388
[papers shuffling]

238
00:21:57,109 --> 00:22:00,112
[breathes heavily]

239
00:22:08,871 --> 00:22:09,872
[door opens]

240
00:22:11,039 --> 00:22:12,040
[assistant] Helena.

241
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:13,917
She's in here, sir.

242
00:22:24,178 --> 00:22:25,179
Helena.

243
00:22:28,140 --> 00:22:29,725
You look so nice.

244
00:22:32,603 --> 00:22:33,645
Like a film.

245
00:22:36,565 --> 00:22:37,566
[Helly] Thank you.

246
00:22:41,445 --> 00:22:46,325
Are you… Are you still in pain?

247
00:22:48,744 --> 00:22:49,745
I'm not.

248
00:22:50,954 --> 00:22:51,955
Not anymore.

249
00:22:58,712 --> 00:23:02,132
I cried in my bed when they told me
what she tried to do to you.

250
00:23:03,258 --> 00:23:05,844
What that innie tried to do. I...

251
00:23:09,723 --> 00:23:11,558
Thank you for going through with this.

252
00:23:13,143 --> 00:23:15,479
The Grandfather would cherish
what you've done.

253
00:23:17,397 --> 00:23:21,443
And one day you will sit with me
at my revolving.

254
00:23:25,113 --> 00:23:26,323
Are you feeling well?

255
00:23:27,824 --> 00:23:28,825
Yeah.

256
00:23:29,326 --> 00:23:33,747
I think, uh... I think
the drink just hit me a little bit.

257
00:23:35,499 --> 00:23:37,334
You'll be all right for the speech?

258
00:23:39,378 --> 00:23:41,505
For my speech. Yeah. Of course.

259
00:23:44,925 --> 00:23:48,095
Do you remember when I brought home
the first chip to show you?

260
00:23:50,556 --> 00:23:51,640
The prototype.

261
00:23:53,851 --> 00:23:56,186
It had the blue and green lights
back then.

262
00:23:58,063 --> 00:23:59,064
Yeah.

263
00:24:00,816 --> 00:24:04,903
I remember you said to me,
"It's so pretty, Daddy.

264
00:24:06,655 --> 00:24:09,199
Everybody in the whole world
should get one."

265
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:12,703
They will.

266
00:24:15,455 --> 00:24:16,540
Because of you.

267
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:22,004
They'll all be Kier's children.

268
00:24:22,546 --> 00:24:29,011
- [footsteps approaching]
- [door opens] [Natalie] Mr. Eagan. Helena. It's time to head to stage.

269
00:24:54,036 --> 00:24:58,415
[whispers] Forgive me
for the harm I've caused this world.

270
00:25:00,375 --> 00:25:05,756
None may atone for my actions… but me.

271
00:25:09,176 --> 00:25:13,305
And only in me shall their stain live on.

272
00:25:16,975 --> 00:25:18,852
All I can be is sorry.

273
00:25:20,604 --> 00:25:22,231
And that is all I am.

274
00:25:42,543 --> 00:25:44,086
[sighs]

275
00:26:26,461 --> 00:26:28,088
[engine starts]

276
00:26:44,021 --> 00:26:45,022
[tires screech]

277
00:27:06,502 --> 00:27:08,262
[Devon] You swear
you're not fucking with me?

278
00:27:09,004 --> 00:27:10,005
I swear.

279
00:27:11,131 --> 00:27:13,008
This is so insane.

280
00:27:13,091 --> 00:27:15,928
They need to send people down
to check every inch of that place.

281
00:27:16,011 --> 00:27:19,515
Like, inspectors or whatever.
Is that a thing? Inspectors?

282
00:27:19,598 --> 00:27:21,141
Yeah. There are inspectors.

283
00:27:22,142 --> 00:27:27,523
Mark has b... I mean, out here, you have been trying to figure out what Lumon does. What you do.

284
00:27:27,606 --> 00:27:28,607
Okay.

285
00:27:31,568 --> 00:27:36,698
I just… I just want to know why.

286
00:27:38,325 --> 00:27:40,327
Why he put me in there.

287
00:27:45,082 --> 00:27:47,084
[sighs] He lost his wife.

288
00:27:47,751 --> 00:27:51,171
You lost your wife.
A little before you started at Lumon.

289
00:27:52,297 --> 00:27:53,966
- Gemma.
- Mm-hmm.

290
00:27:55,467 --> 00:28:00,305
It was a car accident, and,
at first, you tried to keep teaching.

291
00:28:01,682 --> 00:28:02,975
I was a teacher?

292
00:28:03,058 --> 00:28:05,477
A professor. Of history.

293
00:28:05,561 --> 00:28:12,568
[inhales sharply] You tried to go back
to teaching three weeks after she died, and it was a disaster.

294
00:28:14,027 --> 00:28:16,864
She was just still in your veins,
you know?

295
00:28:17,406 --> 00:28:18,532
Making everything hurt.

296
00:28:20,617 --> 00:28:24,162
Which is why I guess you thought
the severed job would...

297
00:28:26,957 --> 00:28:28,959
He hoped you'd be spared from the pain.

298
00:28:38,218 --> 00:28:39,636
It's a nice name. Gemma.

299
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,721
[Devon chuckles]

300
00:28:41,889 --> 00:28:44,016
[chuckles] Yeah.

301
00:28:46,059 --> 00:28:48,770
We were all really close. It was great.

302
00:28:50,564 --> 00:28:51,857
She was wonderful.

303
00:28:53,358 --> 00:28:54,568
She made you wonderful.

304
00:29:29,478 --> 00:29:31,313
[tires squealing]

305
00:29:39,071 --> 00:29:40,071
[ringing]

306
00:29:43,033 --> 00:29:44,660
They told me not to talk to you.

307
00:29:44,743 --> 00:29:49,331
The goddamn OTC's been triggered!
Mark S. is his fucking innie!

308
00:29:49,414 --> 00:29:50,541
What? That's not possible.

309
00:29:50,624 --> 00:29:51,834
[tires squealing]

310
00:29:52,501 --> 00:29:55,003
It's Dylan.
They've been plotting this all along.

311
00:29:55,087 --> 00:29:56,296
Helly's at the gala.

312
00:29:56,380 --> 00:30:00,217
I'll take care of Helly.
I'll fix it like I fix everything.

313
00:30:01,009 --> 00:30:04,638
Get to the security office,
and shut it off now!

314
00:30:04,721 --> 00:30:06,139
Shit!

315
00:30:23,073 --> 00:30:24,073
[beeps]

316
00:30:25,367 --> 00:30:27,244
Goddamn it! Dylan!

317
00:30:27,744 --> 00:30:28,744
Dylan!

318
00:30:29,663 --> 00:30:31,665
I know you're in there, Dylan.
Open the door!

319
00:30:31,748 --> 00:30:33,834
Fuck you, Mr. Milchick!

320
00:30:34,543 --> 00:30:37,004
Dylan! Dylan!

321
00:30:38,964 --> 00:30:40,942
Ricken knows a lot of high-end journalists
in New York.

322
00:30:40,966 --> 00:30:43,051
And you think that's better
than the police?

323
00:30:43,135 --> 00:30:45,679
Well, Lumon has their hands
in so many pies.

324
00:30:45,762 --> 00:30:47,347
Sorry, do you understand metaphor?

325
00:30:47,431 --> 00:30:49,183
Yeah, hands in pies. I get it.

326
00:30:49,266 --> 00:30:51,560
I think we have to be really careful
about who we talk to.

327
00:30:51,643 --> 00:30:53,437
- Okay.
- How much time do you have?

328
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:55,189
I don't know. Maybe an hour?

329
00:30:55,272 --> 00:31:01,361
Right. Because once your bosses find out… Jesus, I totally forgot. Cobel! Why is Cobel here?

330
00:31:01,445 --> 00:31:02,654
What?

331
00:31:02,738 --> 00:31:05,490
My boss from Lumon. Ms. Cobel.
She's at this party.

332
00:31:05,574 --> 00:31:06,700
What are you talking about?

333
00:31:06,783 --> 00:31:08,744
I mean, she's dressed different.

334
00:31:08,827 --> 00:31:11,830
Kind of a flowy, purple outfit,
silver hair.

335
00:31:13,207 --> 00:31:15,042
Mark, are you talking about Mrs. Selvig?

336
00:31:15,542 --> 00:31:17,878
Maybe, but her name is Harmony Cobel.

337
00:31:18,378 --> 00:31:20,047
And she works at Lumon?

338
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:21,256
Yeah, she's my boss.

339
00:31:21,340 --> 00:31:22,508
Jesus fucking Christ.

340
00:31:50,619 --> 00:31:51,787
[Mr. Milchick] Dylan.

341
00:31:51,870 --> 00:31:53,163
Why are you doing this, man?

342
00:31:53,997 --> 00:31:54,998
Come on.

343
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:58,794
You are the refiner of the quarter!

344
00:31:58,877 --> 00:32:03,274
[Ricken] "While most cultures view sex
as ugly or foul, - I've always seen it..." - Mrs. Selvig?

345
00:32:03,298 --> 00:32:04,984
- What?
- Is she there? Is Mrs. Selvig there?

346
00:32:05,008 --> 00:32:05,843
- Do you...
- What?

347
00:32:05,926 --> 00:32:06,969
Mrs. Selvig?

348
00:32:07,052 --> 00:32:08,971
- What is going on?
- She has Eleanor!

349
00:32:09,054 --> 00:32:12,224
What? Um... Uh...
Excuse me a moment, okay. Um...

350
00:32:12,307 --> 00:32:14,726
Honey? What did you say?

351
00:32:14,810 --> 00:32:17,729
[Devon] Mrs. Selvig has Eleanor.
Did you see her?

352
00:32:20,691 --> 00:32:22,067
- Oh, my God.
- What is going on?

353
00:32:22,150 --> 00:32:23,902
Oh, my God. Her car's gone.

354
00:32:23,986 --> 00:32:26,321
I gave her the baby, and she left!

355
00:32:26,905 --> 00:32:30,242
- She left? With Eleanor?
- [Devon] I handed her the baby, and she left!

356
00:32:30,325 --> 00:32:32,303
- [Ricken] Have we looked everywhere?
- [Devon] Not yet!

357
00:32:32,327 --> 00:32:33,847
[Ricken] Okay, let's...
Let's go inside and look.

358
00:32:33,871 --> 00:32:34,871
Oh, my God!

359
00:32:58,812 --> 00:33:02,232
[panting]
I bet the tempers were disappointed.

360
00:33:02,316 --> 00:33:04,067
I can still get you back in there.

361
00:33:04,568 --> 00:33:06,278
I can get you any perk you want, Dylan.

362
00:33:06,361 --> 00:33:09,198
Hey, there's stuff
you don't even know about.

363
00:33:09,281 --> 00:33:12,910
There's... There's paintball,
there's coffee cozies.

364
00:33:12,993 --> 00:33:14,244
Dylan, come on!

365
00:33:15,412 --> 00:33:18,498
Just say the word, and I'll get you
a coffee cozy literally right now, Dylan.

366
00:33:18,582 --> 00:33:19,625
Come on, man!

367
00:33:19,708 --> 00:33:23,378
I wanna remember
my fucking kid being born!

368
00:33:25,547 --> 00:33:27,216
You have two others.

369
00:33:28,425 --> 00:33:29,635
I can tell you about 'em.

370
00:33:30,928 --> 00:33:32,614
Open the door,
and I'll tell you their names.

371
00:33:32,638 --> 00:33:33,638
Come on, Dylan.

372
00:33:34,765 --> 00:33:36,725
- [breathes heavily]
- [Mr. Milchick] Dylan!

373
00:33:48,362 --> 00:33:49,363
[tires squealing]

374
00:33:51,073 --> 00:33:52,491
[tires squealing]

375
00:34:08,757 --> 00:34:10,509
[valet] Whoa, whoa, whoa. It's rolling.

376
00:34:12,427 --> 00:34:15,848
[Helly] My name is Helena,
and I'm an Eagan. [chuckles]

377
00:34:16,431 --> 00:34:23,105
So one of the things you learn growing up
as an Eagan is that the workers… - [coordinator] We start in two minutes. - Thanks.

378
00:34:23,188 --> 00:34:24,188
Good luck.

379
00:34:25,899 --> 00:34:28,652
I'll tee you up.
Just stick to the talking points.

380
00:34:28,735 --> 00:34:31,655
Use the line about
how you see your innie as your sister.

381
00:34:31,737 --> 00:34:33,574
- They'll love that. [chuckles]
- Got it.

382
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:35,617
It's gonna be great.

383
00:35:20,954 --> 00:35:22,581
She's not in the baby room.

384
00:35:23,165 --> 00:35:24,875
Have all these rooms been checked?

385
00:35:25,959 --> 00:35:27,586
[Eleanor crying]

386
00:35:27,669 --> 00:35:29,046
[Patton] Oh, thank God.

387
00:35:29,129 --> 00:35:30,631
Devon! I got her!

388
00:35:31,131 --> 00:35:34,259
Devon, she's here! I found her.

389
00:35:34,343 --> 00:35:35,761
I found your child.

390
00:35:36,929 --> 00:35:52,861
- I'm the one who found her!
- [crying fades] [Mr. Milchick] Dylan!

391
00:35:55,030 --> 00:35:56,323
Dylan!

392
00:35:56,406 --> 00:36:04,414
[Natalie] …improvements in morale, - a happier workplace. - [breathes heavily] As with any transformative technology, there have been setbacks.

393
00:36:04,498 --> 00:36:05,624
Bumps in the road.

394
00:36:05,707 --> 00:36:10,003
But I'm here tonight to tell you
that we are on the verge of a revolution.

395
00:36:10,087 --> 00:36:17,553
A kind and empathetic revolution that puts the human being… - Oh, my God! [breathes heavily] - Is it you?

396
00:36:18,220 --> 00:36:20,722
[stammers] What are you talking about?

397
00:36:21,223 --> 00:36:24,643
[exhales sharply] It is you, isn't it?

398
00:36:24,726 --> 00:36:29,022
- [breathes shakily]
- I'm gonna kill your company.

399
00:36:29,106 --> 00:36:30,107
[Ms. Cobel gasps]

400
00:36:30,190 --> 00:36:31,608
Your company!

401
00:36:32,526 --> 00:36:35,112
Who the hell do you think you are?

402
00:36:35,195 --> 00:36:38,156
No. Your friends are gonna suffer.

403
00:36:39,157 --> 00:36:41,368
Mark will suffer.

404
00:36:41,451 --> 00:36:49,042
You'll be long gone, but we will keep them alive, in pain.

405
00:36:49,626 --> 00:36:50,794
You're on.

406
00:36:50,878 --> 00:36:53,213
[Natalie] …decided
that we could do better.

407
00:36:53,297 --> 00:37:01,305
He may never have seen
a severance chip in his lifetime, but it represents his gentle and elegant vision made manifest.

408
00:37:01,388 --> 00:37:04,641
But why don't we hear from someone
who can tell us all about it firsthand?

409
00:37:06,852 --> 00:37:11,607
Ladies and gentlemen, our guest of honor, Helena Eagan. [chuckles]

410
00:37:18,405 --> 00:37:19,615
Thank you, Natalie.

411
00:37:25,245 --> 00:37:26,246
[gasps]

412
00:37:50,312 --> 00:37:51,438
Devon!

413
00:37:56,068 --> 00:37:57,236
[Helly] My name is Helly R.

414
00:37:58,779 --> 00:38:00,030
I'm an innie.

415
00:38:01,698 --> 00:38:04,618
And everything they've told you
about severance is a lie!

416
00:38:04,701 --> 00:38:05,702
Devon!

417
00:38:08,205 --> 00:38:09,873
Burt!

418
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:12,334
Burt!

419
00:38:12,417 --> 00:38:15,712
No, no, no. Listen, we're not happy.
We're miserable.

420
00:38:17,130 --> 00:38:18,590
Burt!

421
00:38:19,716 --> 00:38:23,387
- [grunting, screaming]
- They torture us down there!

422
00:38:23,971 --> 00:38:25,305
[Irving] Burt!

423
00:38:25,389 --> 00:38:27,850
Devon! Please!

424
00:38:28,976 --> 00:38:30,060
We're prisoners!

425
00:38:31,436 --> 00:38:33,230
She's alive!

426
00:38:33,730 --> 00:38:34,815
[Dylan grunts]

427
00:38:35,274 --> 00:38:36,275
Burt!

428
00:38:39,236 --> 00:38:40,571
[elevator bell dings]

429
00:38:40,595 --> 00:38:42,595
